Brazil’s PMDB May Contest 2014 Presidential Race, Estado Says

-- B y   A l e x a n d e r   C u a d r o s
-- 
2011-05-07T15:41:04Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-07/brazil-s-pmdb-may-contest-2014-presidential-race-estado-says.html
The Brazilian Democratic Movement
Party, the government’s main coalition partner, may run its own
candidate in the 2014 presidential election,  O Estado de S.
Paulo  reported, citing party head Valdir Raupp.  Brazil Vice President Michel Temer or Rio de Janeiro state
Governor Sergio Cabral may represent the PMDB, as the party is
known, in the race, Estado cited Senator Raupp as saying.  Press officials representing Temer and Cabral told the Sao
Paulo-based newspaper that both politicians expect the alliance
between the PMDB and President Dilma Rousseff’s Workers’ Party
to be maintained.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alexander Cuadros in Sao Paulo at 
 acuadros@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Papadopoulos in New York at 
 papadopoulous@bloomberg.net  